algebraic datatype = description of data
structural recursion -> approach to mechanically transform
algebraic datatypes
trait = interface with default methods
traits are abstractions over classes

In accordance with uniform access principle,
traits can feature def which can be overloaded as defs/vals/vars / constructor parameters,
for example in case classes
also traits can define val, but it is less used

traits can be sealed, meaning extended only in current file, this is used very often
pattern matching with missing extends cases will issue a warning
classes can be sealed and final